FT  19 MAY 94 / Call to change car numbering format
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A move to change the car registration plate format, with its annual prefix
letter, is being launched by the Society of Motor Manufacturers and Traders.
The current system, which will see the introduction of M-prefixed plates on
August 1, continues to create problems for motor traders and car makers
because of the huge sales bulge it causes in August, Mr Peter Ward, the
society's new president who is chairman and chief executive of Rolls-Royce
Motor Cars, said yesterday.
August accounts for nearly a quarter of the year's total sales, but Mr Ward
said the month had a depressing effect on sales as early as May.
