<HEADLINE>
FT  18 MAY 94 / Observer: Flagwaver
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
It sounds like Geoffrey Martin, the acting head of the European Commission's
London outpost, has finally got the job as the EC's official London
flagwaver.
A year has passed since John Drew quit the job and there has been strong
pressure to reserve the post for a friendly Tory MEP who failed to win
re-election next month.
Martin, 53, an Ulsterman, is not the normal kind of Brussels bureaucrat. He
was president of the National Union of Students while at Belfast's Queen's
University, then ran the housing charity, Shelter, and worked for the
Commonwealth Secretariat before joining the Commission.
A European-friendly equivalent of Des Wilson, perhaps?
</TEXT>
<XX>
Countries:-
</XX>
<CN>GBZ  United Kingdom, EC.
</CN>
<XX>
Industries:-
</XX>
<IN>P9721 International Affairs.
</IN>
