not change the fact that the economies of scale in the industry casts doubt
on the future of the smaller independents.'
The existing practice throughout the mobile industry is to subsidise the
acquisition of subscribers. Mr Cruickshank ruled that 'mature' service
providers should make a reasonable return on this investment, defined as two
per cent a month over 35 months.
