fees out of the income stream from dividends, the Securities and Investments
Board, the City's chief watchdog, said yesterday.
SIB has been under pressure from the unit trust industry to alter new rules
on unit trust pricing which had restricted the source from which fees could
be derived. It said it was 'not expressing a view on the appropriateness of
adopting the practice of charging to capital'.
