<HEADLINE>
FT  18 MAY 94 / World Trade News: ABB in Dollars 100m German deal
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By AP-DJ
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   ZURICH
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Asea Brown Boveri, the Swiss-Swedish heavy engineering group, said it
received an order valued at around Dollars 100m (Pounds 66m) to supply and
install components for a residual waste incineration plant at Niehl, near
Cologne in Germany, AP-DJ reports from Zurich.
The order was placed by LC Steinmueller of Gummersbach, the general
contractors who are responsible for the turn-key delivery of the plant, the
company said.
ABB said the plant, which is scheduled to start operating in 1997, would be
run by AVG, a waste exploitation and disposal company based in Cologne.
