</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
US and Japanese negotiators will meet on Thursday in Washington to seek a
way to restart trade talks stalled since February, US Trade Representative
Mickey Kantor said yesterday, AP reports from Washington.
Mr Kantor told reporters the discussions would follow preliminary talks he
held with then-Foreign Minister Tsutomu Hata last month in Morocco. He gave
no indication who would lead the Japanese delegation. Mr Hata, now prime
minister, has let it be known he wants to resume the negotiations, known as
'framework talks', aimed at opening Japan's markets in areas ranging from
cars to medical equipment.
